    = title 'JSpec', 'Rails Integration'

    %p
      No additional gems are required for JSpec to integrate with Ruby on Rails. Simply initialize
      a project using the command below at the root of your Rails project:
      
    %pre $ jspec init --rails
    
    %p
      JSpec will create a 'jspec' directory, and ... your done! The rest of JSpec's functionality
      is exactly the same, get started by binding JSpec using the command below and edit
      'public/javascripts/application.js' (or any other JS) and JSpec will run your specifications.
      
    %pre $ jspec
    
    %p
      Alternatively just as you may with regular JSpec projects, run your specs using Rhino:
      
    %pre jspec run --rhino
    
    %p
      Or bind with Rhino
      
    %pre jspec --rhino

